    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hyland</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 80.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States of America,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bermuda,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 25, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to inform you that the British
                    brig Eagle, Captain Norfolk, sailed from this port on the 22d instant for
                    Liverpool, Great Britain, with a cargo of cotton, taken from warehouse here, and
                    a large portion of bar silver from the rebel steamship Florida, the whole valued
                    at £50,000. The silver has been transferred by bill of sale to John J. Bourne,
                    the agent of the rebel States.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, with much respect, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. C. J. HYLAND, <hi rend="italic">Vice-Consul.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
